DC  Porphyrin and chlorophyll metabolism
DR  KEGG; map00860;
CC  This pathway for the biosynthesis of 5-aminolevulinate, a porphyrin
CC  precursor, is known as the glutamate or C5 pathway and is found in most
CC  bacteria. A distinctive feature of this pathway is the utilization of
CC  an amino acid-charged tRNA as an enzymatic substrate.  An alternative
CC  pathway from succinyl-CoA and glycine utilizing 5-aminolevulinate
CC  synthase is found in the alphaproteobacteria and eukaryotic
CC  mitochondria[1,2,3].
**  Evidence for step 2 is also used for GP0258 and GP0800.
**  Evidence for step 2 is also used for GP0258 and GP0831.
